# 🔍 Needle

Needle is a lightweight command-line search engine written in Java that helps users quickly find text within local files.

The goal of the project is to explore core Java concepts such as object-oriented programming, file handling, collections, and exception handling by building a practical tool from scratch.

## Features

### Current
- Search for a word or phrase in text files
- Display which files contain the search term
- Simple command-line interface
- Case-insensitive searching

### Planned
- Count the number of matches in each file
- Display matching lines with line numbers
- Support searching multiple words
- Build a searchable index for faster lookups
- Filter searches by file extension
- Recursive folder searching
- Improved result ranking

## Why I Built This

I wanted to move beyond typical beginner projects like library or student management systems and build something that solves a real problem while strengthening my Java skills.

Needle is also part of my portfolio for developing practical software engineering and problem-solving experience.

## Technologies

- Java
- Object-Oriented Programming
- Collections Framework
- File I/O
- Exception Handling

## Example

Searching for:

```
java
```

Could produce:

```
Found 3 matching files:

guide.txt
notes.txt
tutorial.txt
```

Future versions may display:

```
guide.txt (8 matches)
notes.txt (2 matches)
tutorial.txt (1 match)
```

## Learning Goals

This project is designed to help me practice:

- Designing classes and methods
- Reading and processing files
- Working with collections
- Handling exceptions gracefully
- Building maintainable command-line applications
- Incrementally improving software through multiple versions

## Project Status

🚧 In active development.

The project is intentionally being built in small, understandable phases with a focus on learning rather than rushing features.

